|GKB-- Sacred Grove -----------------------------------------------|000

A Sacred Grove is a druid's living anchor in the wild.  Plant it
once, tend it over time, and use it as a place for ritual work,
recovery, and return.

|GKB-- Commands ---------------------------------------------------|000

  |CKBgrove plant                         |000 Root your grove here.
  |CKBgrove                               |000 Show grove status in this room.
  |CKBcommune                             |000 Return to your own grove.
  |CKBcommune to <name>                   |000 Visit a mature public grove.
  |CKBgroves                              |000 List mature groves open to guests.
  |CKBgrove stash                         |000 Legacy stash status.
  |CKBout                                 |000 Leave your inner sanctum.

|GKB-- Planting ---------------------------------------------------|000

Use |CKBgrove plant|000 in the wild.  City rooms and inside rooms
cannot hold a Sacred Grove.  The grove token remains in that
wilderness anchor; nurture and regen pulses begin there.

|GKB-- Growth -----------------------------------------------------|000

  |CKBStage 0-2|000  Young grove.  Anchor only.
  |CKBStage 3  |000  Mature grove.  Commune enters an inner sanctum.
  |CKBStage 4  |000  Ancient grove.  Inner sanctum is safe sanctuary.

When the grove becomes mature, |CKBcommune|000 takes you into a
private spirit-room tied to your grove instead of the shared
wilderness tile.  Use |CKBout|000 to step back to the wild anchor.

Ancient groves carry full sanctuary law.  Younger mature groves use
the same kind of spirit-room, but combat is not forbidden there.

|GKB-- Guests -----------------------------------------------------|000

Guests may use |CKBcommune to <name>|000 once the host grove is
mature.  Use the full player name if it has spaces, for example:

  |CKBcommune to anna marie|000

Guests share the host's inner sanctum.  Guest travel fails if the
anchor is barred, no-teleport, or otherwise unsafe for grove travel.
Two PK druids who are not in the same party cannot commune to each
other's groves.

|GKB-- Profession Materials ---------------------------------------|000

Druid rites now use saved profession materials instead of the old
Grove stash.  Use |CKBreagents|000 and |CKBreagents search <item>|000
to inspect what you carry.  Any old stash contents are migrated into
profession materials when possible.

Leaving the Druid guild removes your grove registration, destroys the
anchor token, and releases the sanctum.

|GKB-- Limits -----------------------------------------------------|000

You cannot commune while fighting or from a no-teleport room.  Guest
commune also refuses barred paths such as guild halls, player housing
paths, and similar protected areas.

|RKBNote:|000 |CKBcommune|000 and |CKBgrove plant|000 use room
spell-limit cooldowns internally.
